This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as sentiment analysis and relation extraction. Additionally, the use of neural networks for these tasks suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) and "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which could place it in the sub-category of "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of neural networks for optimization and performance improvement could also suggest that it belongs to the sub-category of "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
